<h2>Latest news:</h2>

<p><strong>May 27, 2011</strong><br />
  KDE SC 4.6.3 was <a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-kde/2011/05/msg00034.html">uploaded to
  unstable</a>. Enjoy!
</p>

<p><strong>February 6, 2011</strong><br />
  <a href="http://www.debian.org/News/2011/20110205a">Squeeze was released</a>
  with KDE 4.4.5. Testing repos will keep KDE 4.4.5 <a href=http://lists.debian.org/1296956851.16209.5044.camel@hathi.jungle.funky-badger.org>until beginnings of March</a>
 (see "Onwards with Wheezy", third paragraph).
</p>

<p><strong>August 24, 2010</strong><br />
  As <a href="http://www.debian.org/News/2010/20100806">Squeeze has been
  frozen</a>, Debian will ship Squeeze with KDE 4.4.5. Unstable repos will have
  4.4.5 too until Squeeze release. KDE 4.5.x will be available via other repo
  some time later.
</p>

<p><strong>May 16, 2010</strong><br />
   Debian testing users can finally enjoy a release from the KDE Software
   Compilation 4.4.x series! KDE SC 4.4.3 has found its way to Debian testing.
</p>

<p><strong>May 3, 2010</strong><br />
   After long months of waiting, Debian unstable users can finally enjoy
   a release from the KDE Software Compilation 4.4.x series! KDE SC 4.4.3 has
   found its way to Debian unstable.
</p>

<p><strong>April 22, 2010</strong><br />
   KDE 4.4.2 is available from experimental.
</p>

<p><strong>February 22, 2010</strong><br />
     Finally the team decided KDE SC 4.4.0 will not make it to the archive, but 4.4.1 (to be released
	 on the 2nd of March) probably will land in experimental/unstable.
</p>

<p><strong>February 17, 2010</strong><br />
     KDE 4.4.0 is being worked on but it will take some time until it lands on your Debian mirror.
</p>

